cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses capturing sensor data using mobile phones and the Internet of Things vision. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the paper mentions participatory sensing, which involves multiple agents (mobile phones) working together to sense the environment. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of a middleware component to process sensor data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a prototype application and middleware component. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on data structures or algorithms, but rather on the capture and processing of sensor data.
